                            <comment id="14084922" author="tdunning" created="Mon, 4 Aug 2014 18:23:33 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;Is the comment wrong or is the code wrong?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sounds like it may actually be the comment.  I say this because&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
sqrt(sum (x_i - y_i)^2)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is the distance between vectors.  The root-mean-square distance is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
sqrt(1/n * sum (x_i - y_i)^2)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Converting a distance d into a similarity can plausibly be done using&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
1/(1+d)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
1/(1+d^2)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or even &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
1/d
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(if all vectors are distinct)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The idea is to use a form which has a maximum where distance is minimized.  With distances, you want to preserve qualities like the triangle inequality, but not so much for similarities.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This looks to me more like your &quot;incorrect&quot; version and that makes it seem like there might be fault with the comment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
